SECTION 1 — DEFINITIONS

1.1 "Software" means the NoteArmor Secured Notepad Pro application in its
    entirety, including but not limited to: all Python source files, compiled
    extension modules (.pyd), Qt resource files, QSS stylesheets, icon assets,
    binary assets, documentation, and associated configuration files.

1.2 "Author" means PatronHubDevs Technologies and its principal developer,
    Marco Polo, and any authorized contributors.

1.3 "Licensee" means any individual or entity exercising rights under this
    License.

1.4 "Personal Use" means use by a natural person (human individual) solely
    for private, recreational, educational, or research purposes that do not
    generate any direct or indirect commercial benefit, revenue, or
    compensation of any kind.

1.5 "Commercial Use" means any use, deployment, distribution, or integration
    of the Software intended to generate revenue, reduce costs, support a
    business operation, or provide commercial advantage, including but not
    limited to:
      - Selling or licensing the Software or a derivative thereof
      - Deploying the Software as part of a paid product or service
      - Using the Software to process data for clients or customers
      - Offering the Software as a hosted or SaaS solution
      - Including the Software in a commercial bundle or installer

1.6 "Derivative Work" means any work that is based on or incorporates the
    Software, or any portion thereof, including modifications, translations,
    adaptations, abridgements, or any other form in which the Software may
    be recast, transformed, or adapted.

1.7 "Distribution" means making the Software or a Derivative Work available
    to any third party by any means, including electronic transfer, physical
    media, or web publication.

