    Use as defined in Section 1.5.

3.2 DISTRIBUTION
    You may not distribute, publish, upload, post, transmit, or otherwise
    make available the Software or any Derivative Work to any third party,
    whether in source or binary form.

3.3 SUBLICENSING
    You may not grant sublicenses to the Software or any portion thereof.

3.4 REBRANDING AND MISREPRESENTATION
    You may not rebrand, rename, or otherwise represent the Software as your
    own creation. You may not remove, alter, or obscure any copyright notices,
    authorship attribution, license notices, or trademark designations
    contained in the Software.

3.5 SAAS AND HOSTED DEPLOYMENT
    You may not deploy the Software or any Derivative Work as a cloud-based,
    web-hosted, or Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) offering accessible to
    third parties.

3.6 COMPETITIVE USE
    You may not use the Software, its source code, architecture, encryption
    logic, file format specification, or UI design as a reference or basis
    for developing a competing product or service without express written
    consent from the Author.

3.7 DECOMPILATION OF PROTECTED MODULES
    You may not reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, or otherwise
    attempt to derive the source code of the compiled extension module
    `core/encryption.pyd` or any other compiled binary component of the
    Software.

3.8 AUTOMATED DEPLOYMENT OR REDISTRIBUTION
    You may not include the Software in automated provisioning systems,
    enterprise deployment tools, app stores, software repositories, package
    managers, or similar systems without written authorization from the Author.

